<s docid="FT944-15057" num="4"> FT 20 OCT 94 / Improved ferry safety urged</s>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<s docid="FT944-15057" num="5"> The Royal Institution of Naval Architects yesterday called for urgent action to improve safety standards on roll-on-roll-off passenger ferries.</s>

<s docid="FT944-15057" num="6"> The sinking of the ferry Estonia in the Baltic last month with the loss of more than 900 lives gave added weight to the call for tighter standards, it said.</s>

<s docid="FT944-15057" num="7"> The institution first made a plea for improvements in 1988.</s>
